Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.39,0:28:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of a sudden everything is like\Nincredible technically it's like God was
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.32,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that beautiful profound stillness seems\Nto prevail over all things and light
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,starts to come from within yourself and\Nyou realize that's who you are. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.08,0:28:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,time to let your friends know that\Nyou're spiritually very serious
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.73,0:29:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\Nbecause someday while in the middle of a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.55,0:29:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,bagel you suddenly get blissed out and\Nand uh they call the doctors you had a
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.12,0:29:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,tonic or bliss out or what that\Nchiridananda you know can be very
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.60,0:29:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,paralyzing I've been in it and uh you\Nyou cannot function there's no desire to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.08,0:29:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,function where the body falls over and\Nand dies so much the better. You
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.39,0:29:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't care less. It's not a reality.\NAnd if you still have an attachment to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.08,0:29:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,love, not love itself, but an attachment\Nto love, you make make I I consider an
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.36,0:29:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,error to well, no, I won't consider an\Nerror. Not an error. It was the right
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.36,0:29:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,thing to do decide to do it for the sake\Nof someone else to come back in the body
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.67,0:29:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and resume life.\NNo, it's not an error. But uh
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.55,0:29:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't have to go back and\Nbackfill. uh because you suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.24,0:29:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend whole. You see, you can go\Nthere from the pits of hell. In this
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.91,0:30:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,experience here, it was at the pits of\Nhell. It must have been
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.03,0:30:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,oh lower than here. The pits of hell are\Ndown below here. Uh I don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.08,0:30:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,scare people and tell them what it's\Nlike there. But anyway, the pits, you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.44,0:30:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can go from the pits of hell up to an\Nextremely high state and bypass all of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.08,0:30:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NUh why is that? Because the ego is not a
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.15,0:30:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. You have to undo that which\Ndoesn't exist. You just have to bypass
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.76,0:30:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it. You don't have to disassemble the\Nego because it's only illusion that that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.96,0:30:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,keeps it in place.\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.00,0:30:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,how many no\Nit you can go up hundreds and hundreds
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.96,0:30:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of points in an instant.\NAnd well, it isn't just an instant, but
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.48,0:30:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all of a sudden the landscape changes\Nand one's reality changes. Sense of who
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.39,0:30:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you are changes and one has just\Ntranscended all of it. Now that state
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.08,0:31:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,may not last in the beginning. Spiritual\Nworkers get discouraged because they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.39,0:31:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,go into a really great state and then\Ndisappears.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.84,0:31:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Though that's the black knight of the\Nsoul and the Christian saints, a number
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.55,0:31:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of them have written about it. St. and\Nperson and that person. Um, oh woe
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.48,0:31:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,lover, where I have you left me in\Ndestitute and uh blackness and despair
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.12,0:31:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nthe presence is so exquisite that should
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.08,0:31:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,it leave you feel a tremendous sense of\Nloss.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.27,0:31:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the beginning these states may\Ncome but not stay. They may come and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.12,0:31:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,disappear and come and disappear but\Neach one sets each one sets a different
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.27,0:31:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,level of what's possible even though in\Nthe beginning it may not stay. This is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.24,0:31:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,common in Zen meditation. You can go\Ninto a state of sator and then it leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.55,0:31:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you when you get up and walk around the\Nroom. In fact in Sanskrit classically um
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.67,0:32:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these various states have been well\Ncalibrated over the years in Hindu uh in
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.00,0:32:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the Hindu tradition.\NThere are states where uh in meditation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.39,0:32:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you go into an extreme state but then\Nwhen you get up and walk around it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.96,0:32:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears.\NThere's extreme states let's say in the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.91,0:32:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning that only happen when your\Neyes are closed and you lose them if you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.64,0:32:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,open your eyes. Then as you get more\Nadvanced the states of samadei persist
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.64,0:32:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you open your eyes.\NThen as you get more advanced the state
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.96,0:32:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of samadei persist even though you get\Nup and begin to walk around.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.51,0:32:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You get up and walk around and that\Nstate continues.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.36,0:32:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's states beyond that which\Nare permanent and nothing affects it but
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.64,0:32:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but you yes they're permanent but you\Ncan't function. You're per but you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.79,0:32:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,function. Then there is probably the\Nultimate state in which it persists and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.20,0:32:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,yet you are able to function again.\NNothing you do changes the inner
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.08,0:33:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,reality. It is that which is clear and\Nobvious beyond all time. And that which
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.96,0:33:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you are is a very obvious and clear\Nbeyond all time. But by forcing one's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.84,0:33:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,attention on a detail, you can force\Nyourself to see what is out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.00,0:33:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramano Maharshi described that\Num
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.76,0:33:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and it may have been useful in having in\Nrefunctioning the world. would say the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.12,0:33:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,if you focus your consciousness on the\Nouter world you're more able to you're
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.03,0:33:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,able to function there and if and then\Nyou can withdraw it and it all the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.00,0:33:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,energy goes back into the self. So how\Nto balance all energy being in the self
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.88,0:33:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which may be incapacitating and all\Nenergy being in the world is a matter of
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.15,0:33:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,learning.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.36,0:33:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have the mantra\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.39,0:33:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to remind us the purpose for which we're\Nhere today. Because the mantra mount
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.44,0:34:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,verbally at 740 automatically puts you\Nthere where the great cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.55,0:34:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\N>> The exquisite beauty world
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.11,0:34:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,>> shines forth.\N>> [music and singing]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.65,0:34:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,[music and singing]\N>> Then one sees the divinity of all that
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.67,0:34:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,exists.\NThe expression of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.16,0:34:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\Nis God manifesting himself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.35,0:34:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as that which you are in the present.\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.76,0:34:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh\Nmy [music]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.54,0:34:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[singing]\Nshe
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.78,0:34:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.33,0:35:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,[singing]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.28,0:35:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh [singing]\Nshe [music]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.08,0:35:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,>> [singing]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.29,0:35:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,[singing]\N>> Thank you very much and we'll reconvene
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.07,0:35:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in an hour. [music]\N[singing]
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.00,0:35:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> God bless you all.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.72,0:35:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,>> First question is, what is the one thing\NI still want in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.90,0:35:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> [laughter]\N>> Will the artist please stand up? Who is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.44,0:35:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it? Where are you?\N>> Every time, every meeting, he brings me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.83,0:35:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,something incredible. A t-shirt with my\Npast lives. Uh today we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.64,0:36:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,scripture. Uh and uh a 46 Lincoln\NContinental
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.16,0:36:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in stained glass. I mean, that's quite\Nstunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.16,0:36:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The ice shovel is by habit you let go of\Neverything you want as you the wanting
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.40,0:36:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,goes up. So I might have just\Ndisappeared the continental.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.35,0:36:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see. I still want the continental\Nresist. Oh, I hung on to it. [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.88,0:36:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, I got scared there for a second.\NHe goes illusion is if you don't want
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.00,0:36:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you won't get it. You know what I\Nmean? [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.59,0:36:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That wanting it is what gets it for you.\NSo the way I prevent it is I keep
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.64,0:36:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting it which prevents it from\Nhappening in my life and then I won't be
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.64,0:36:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to it. [laughter]\NUm in talking about spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.48,0:37:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there's some things I think about you\Nknow that I should have said.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.48,0:37:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One is when you're making when you get\Ninto a it's like the energy of spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.88,0:37:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,work um keeps getting stronger and\Nstronger. Finally, one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.07,0:37:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,decides to really go for the final run.\NYou know what I'm saying? [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.40,0:37:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What that really consists of is a fixity\Nof attention. a relentless
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.44,0:37:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh staying with it. Let's see how I'm\Nnot expressing that correctly verbally.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.72,0:37:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Um\Nsome people say, "Well, I've done
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.48,0:37:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work on and off for 30 years\Nand I'm still where I was." Well, they
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.48,0:37:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,meditate a little there, they pray a\Nlittle there, they go to a workshop
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.83,0:37:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,there, they hear a speaker there, they\Nread that. It's all sort of sporadic.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.40,0:38:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NThat's all right. When you have time,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.48,0:38:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say you're quite a bit in the\Nworld and you're accumulating data that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.20,0:38:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you're going to use at a later\Ndate, certain understandings, certain
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.68,0:38:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehensions come about.\NBut then there comes a time when
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.40,0:38:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to do whatever practice you're\Ndoing without exception all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.72,0:38:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A very high state can arise\Nin temporal time rather brief if one is
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.35,0:38:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,committedly persistent.\NThe devotion to the truth becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.40,0:38:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,overwhelming.\NThe love for God pulls you. It isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.83,0:38:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're driving it. It's now you're\Nbeing pulled by your own destiny, by
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.83,0:38:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,one's own karmic commitment. Let's say\Nyou've chosen the ultimate destiny. Now
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.00,0:38:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that begins to pull you and attract you.\NIt isn't that you're being driven by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.83,0:39:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being that you're being pulled by\Nit cuz that's your destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.24,0:39:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My guess would be that's the destiny of\Neveryone here. Otherwise, they wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.28,0:39:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,be here.\NThen comes a time for becoming really
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.64,0:39:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,very serious about it. At that point,\Nlet's say you use the technique that I
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.44,0:39:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,uh used the most was uh surrendering and\Nletting go everything as the very moment
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.24,0:39:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it arises. So that what arises in\Nconsciousness is like a wave. It's like
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.32,0:39:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,1/100th of a second it's coming. It\Npeaks and then it leaves. So the letting
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.16,0:39:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,goess is at the peak of it. So that one\Nis constantly like floating over the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.48,0:39:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,waves. In other words, all these\Nthoughts begin to arise and you intuit
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.11,0:39:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it their intention of you and you\Nalready release that intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.32,0:40:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender everything to God. So this\Nbecomes continuous continuous nonstop.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.32,0:40:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember trying to let go of a severe\Nattachment
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.16,0:40:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and for 11 days I sat and did nothing\Nbut let let this go.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.44,0:40:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Every thought, every feeling, every\Nmemory, everything
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.56,0:40:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,as it arose was surrendered.\NYou see, because the energy behind some
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.40,0:40:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughts is accumulated through many\Nlifetimes. The grief that you feel when
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.48,0:40:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you lose a member of your family now is\Nnot just due to losing them. This person
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.20,0:40:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,here and now. It's from all the deaths\Nof all the lifetimes accumulated as an
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.07,0:40:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,accumulation of energy. So when you\Nbegin surrendering that you may pull up
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.28,0:40:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,a major a major one that's accumulated\Nthrough many lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.88,0:40:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This particular one as I say was\Nnon-stop for 11 days morning and night
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.40,0:40:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just went on and on and on and on and\Nfinally it stopped gone forever
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.59,0:41:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,again will you be subject to that. Okay\Nthen arises the next one. So serious
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.00,0:41:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work\Nis a continuous willingness to let
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.56,0:41:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,things go as they arise in the technique\Nthat I share. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.40,0:41:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go, the willingness to\Nsurrender, wanting to control everything
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.31,0:41:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as it arises. The willingness to\Nsurrender, wanting to change it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.83,0:41:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,have it your way, the refusal to\Nsurrender it to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.35,0:41:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Very often one has illusions about the\Nnature of reality that has they have to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,be let go also that there's a good and a\Nbad there's a desirable and undesirable
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.28,0:41:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all in your mind. So\Nyou realize that the sun shines and then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.72,0:41:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the clouds come up and then the rain\Nfalls and the grass grows up and dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.48,0:42:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The stock market goes up and down. Age\Ncomes and goes. People arise and leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.04,0:42:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see there's the eb and flow.\NAnd if one is at this part of the cycle,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.52,0:42:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no point de you know crying\Nabout it because the cycle will cycle
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.76,0:42:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,itself out. You see and by surrendering\Noneself to whatever is cycling up um is
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.07,0:42:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,how one disappears it eventually. You\Ndisappear it by choosing to be with it
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.11,0:42:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and letting go wanting to change it as\Nit arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.92,0:42:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To do that particular technique means to\Ndo it continuously
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.68,0:42:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what non-stop.\NUsually one can do a run for a period
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.92,0:42:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and then of course when you get more\Nadept at it to go back in the ultimate
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.68,0:42:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,state you know it takes about an hour of\Nreleasing all the things that have been
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.44,0:42:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,accumulated and then the state takes\Nover and then but then you're
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.68,0:43:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,immobilized in this in functioning as\Nfar as the world is concerned. See, but
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.52,0:43:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you you know it's close by. And\Nlet's say a wish like wishing to be
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.11,0:43:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehended and understood by all to\Nwhom I'm speaking, you see, has to be
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.83,0:43:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,surrendered because the comprehension of\Nthe truth of what I'm saying is not up
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.92,0:43:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to the speaker. So those illusions arise\Nand as they arise, you let them go. That
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.07,0:43:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the comprehension of what is being said\Nis up to God and what is being said is
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.80,0:43:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,up to God. And there isn't any person\Nsaying them in the first place. So
